{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-11",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_11_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "11 - Who Stole the Tarts?",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 1.488,
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 3,
  "page_start_sec": 9.68,
  "page_end_sec": 250.2,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 9.68,
      "end": 10.68,
      "text": "CHAPTER XI."
    },
    {
      "start": 10.68,
      "end": 11.78,
      "text": "WHO STOLE THE TARTS?"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.0,
      "end": 31.26,
      "text": "king was the White Rabbit,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 31.66,
      "end": 34.28,
      "text": "with a trumpet in one hand and a scroll of parchment in the"
    },
    {
      "start": 34.38,
      "end": 34.54,
      "text": "other."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.36,
      "end": 37.3,
      "text": "In the very middle of the court was a table,"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.42,
      "end": 39.24,
      "text": "with a large dish of tarts upon it."
    },
    {
      "start": 39.72,
      "end": 42.96,
      "text": "They looked so good that it made Alice quite hungry to look at them."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.82,
      "end": 44.56,
      "text": "I wish they'd get"
    },
    {
      "start": 44.56,
      "end": 45.18,
      "text": "the trial done,"
    },
    {
      "start": 45.36,
      "end": 45.78,
      "text": "she thought,"
    },
    {
      "start": 45.9,
      "end": 47.32,
      "text": "and hand round the refreshments."
    },
    {
      "start": 48.32,
      "end": 49.36,
      "text": "But there seemed to be no"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.46,
      "end": 50.1,
      "text": "chance of this,"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.24,
      "end": 53.1,
      "text": "so she began looking about her to pass away the time."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.336,
      "end": 55.04,
      "text": "Alice had never"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.14,
      "end": 56.8,
      "text": "been in a court of justice before,"
    },
    {
      "start": 57.26,
      "end": 58.86,
      "text": "but she had read about them in books,"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.02,
      "end": 59.56,
      "text": "and she was"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.68,
      "end": 61.26,
      "text": "quite pleased to find that she knew"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.26,
      "end": 63.02,
      "text": "the name of nearly everything there."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.032,
      "end": 64.56,
      "text": "That's the Judge,"
    },
    {
      "start": 64.8,
      "end": 65.58,
      "text": "she said to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.86,
      "end": 67.34,
      "text": "because of his great wig."
    },
    {
      "start": 68.35,
      "end": 69.14,
      "text": "The Judge,"
    },
    {
      "start": 69.34,
      "end": 69.84,
      "text": "by the way,"
    },
    {
      "start": 69.84,
      "end": 70.4,
      "text": "was the King,"
    },
    {
      "start": 70.56,
      "end": 73.52,
      "text": "and as he wore his crown over the wig he did not"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.56,
      "end": 74.44,
      "text": "look at all comfortable,"
    },
    {
      "start": 74.7,
      "end": 76.3,
      "text": "and it was certainly not becoming."
    },
    {
      "start": 77.72,
      "end": 78.78,
      "text": "And that's the jury-box,"
    },
    {
      "start": 79.06,
      "end": 79.7,
      "text": "thought Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.3,
      "end": 80.92,
      "text": "And those twelve"
    },
    {
      "start": 81.94,
      "end": 83.36,
      "text": "creatures—she was obliged to say creatures,"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.68,
      "end": 84.0,
      "text": "you see,"
    },
    {
      "start": 84.08,
      "end": 84.82,
      "text": "because some of"
    },
    {
      "start": 84.82,
      "end": 88.58,
      "text": "them were animals and some were birds—I suppose they're the jurors,"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.76,
      "end": 89.54,
      "text": "she said this"
    },
    {
      "start": 89.56,
      "end": 91.74,
      "text": "last word two or three times over to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.02,
      "end": 93.54,
      "text": "being rather proud of it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.86,
      "end": 94.36,
      "text": "for she thought,"
    },
    {
      "start": 94.5,
      "end": 95.16,
      "text": "and rightly too,"
    },
    {
      "start": 95.7,
      "end": 99.06,
      "text": "that very few little girls of her age knew the meaning of it at all."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.52,
      "end": 99.78,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 100.04,
      "end": 101.82,
      "text": "jurymen would have done just as well."
    },
    {
      "start": 102.66,
      "end": 105.02,
      "text": "The twelve jurors were all writing very busily"
    },
    {
      "start": 105.02,
      "end": 105.66,
      "text": "on slates."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.94,
      "end": 107.74,
      "text": "What are they all doing?"
    },
    {
      "start": 107.98,
      "end": 109.36,
      "text": "Alice whispered to the griffin."
    },
    {
      "start": 109.9,
      "end": 110.36,
      "text": "They can't have"
    },
    {
      "start": 110.5,
      "end": 112.72,
      "text": "anything to put down yet before the trial's begun."
    },
    {
      "start": 113.96,
      "end": 114.86,
      "text": "They're putting down their names,"
    },
    {
      "start": 115.32,
      "end": 116.74,
      "text": "the griffin whispered in reply"
    },
    {
      "start": 117.44,
      "end": 119.64,
      "text": "for fear they should forget them before the end of the trial"
    },
    {
      "start": 121.024,
      "end": 124.18,
      "text": "stupid things alice began in a loud indignant voice"
    },
    {
      "start": 124.74,
      "end": 126.56,
      "text": "but she stopped hastily for the white"
    },
    {
      "start": 126.64,
      "end": 130.06,
      "text": "rabbit cried out silence in the court and the"
    },
    {
      "start": 130.06,
      "end": 132.44,
      "text": "king put on his spectacles and looked anxiously"
    },
    {
      "start": 132.56,
      "end": 136.72,
      "text": "round to see who was talking alice could see as"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.72,
      "end": 138.54,
      "text": "well as if she were looking over their shoulders"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.54,
      "end": 141.02,
      "text": "that all the jurors were writing down stupid"
    },
    {
      "start": 141.02,
      "end": 143.56,
      "text": "things on their slates and she could even make"
    },
    {
      "start": 143.72,
      "end": 146.2,
      "text": "out that one of them didn't know how to spell stupid,"
    },
    {
      "start": 146.4,
      "end": 148.52,
      "text": "and that he had to ask his neighbor to"
    },
    {
      "start": 148.52,
      "end": 148.9,
      "text": "tell him."
    },
    {
      "start": 149.6,
      "end": 152.26,
      "text": "A nice muddle their slates will be in before the trial's over,"
    },
    {
      "start": 152.44,
      "end": 153.1,
      "text": "thought Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 154.66,
      "end": 156.74,
      "text": "One of the jurors had a pencil that squeaked.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 156.92,
      "end": 157.02,
      "text": "This,"
    },
    {
      "start": 157.68,
      "end": 158.06,
      "text": "of course,"
    },
    {
      "start": 158.14,
      "end": 159.28,
      "text": "Alice could not stand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 159.52,
      "end": 159.86,
      "text": "and she"
    },
    {
      "start": 159.96,
      "end": 161.6,
      "text": "went round the court and got behind him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 161.7,
      "end": 164.52,
      "text": "and very soon found an opportunity of taking it away."
    },
    {
      "start": 165.36,
      "end": 167.63,
      "text": "She did it so quickly that the poor little juror,"
    },
    {
      "start": 167.76,
      "end": 169.16,
      "text": "it was Bill the Lizard,"
    },
    {
      "start": 169.58,
      "end": 170.64,
      "text": "could not make out at all"
    },
    {
      "start": 170.82,
      "end": 171.64,
      "text": "what had become of it."
    },
    {
      "start": 172.14,
      "end": 174.0,
      "text": "So after hunting all about for it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 174.04,
      "end": 175.98,
      "text": "he was obliged to write with one finger"
    },
    {
      "start": 175.98,
      "end": 176.92,
      "text": "for the rest of the day,"
    },
    {
      "start": 177.12,
      "end": 179.16,
      "text": "and this was of very little use,"
    },
    {
      "start": 179.38,
      "end": 180.86,
      "text": "as it left no mark on the slate."
    },
    {
      "start": 181.65,
      "end": 182.3,
      "text": "Harold,"
    },
    {
      "start": 182.52,
      "end": 183.62,
      "text": "read the accusation,"
    },
    {
      "start": 183.74,
      "end": 184.62,
      "text": "said the king."
    },
    {
      "start": 185.64,
      "end": 188.24,
      "text": "On this the white rabbit blew three blasts on the"
    },
    {
      "start": 188.28,
      "end": 188.48,
      "text": "trumpet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 188.62,
      "end": 190.3,
      "text": "and then unrolled the parchment scroll,"
    },
    {
      "start": 190.46,
      "end": 191.28,
      "text": "and read as follows."
    },
    {
      "start": 192.34,
      "end": 193.22,
      "text": "The queen of hearts,"
    },
    {
      "start": 193.4,
      "end": 193.88,
      "text": "she made"
    },
    {
      "start": 194.0,
      "end": 195.72,
      "text": "some tarts all on a summer day."
    },
    {
      "start": 196.38,
      "end": 197.2,
      "text": "The knave of hearts,"
    },
    {
      "start": 197.32,
      "end": 198.52,
      "text": "he stole those tarts,"
    },
    {
      "start": 198.6,
      "end": 199.48,
      "text": "and took them quite"
    },
    {
      "start": 199.66,
      "end": 199.76,
      "text": "away."
    },
    {
      "start": 201.248,
      "end": 201.96,
      "text": "Consider your verdict,"
    },
    {
      "start": 202.2,
      "end": 203.56,
      "text": "the king said to the jury."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.34,
      "end": 204.54,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 204.64,
      "end": 205.16,
      "text": "not yet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 205.3,
      "end": 205.7,
      "text": "not yet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 205.9,
      "end": 206.92,
      "text": "the rabbit hastily"
    },
    {
      "start": 207.0,
      "end": 207.44,
      "text": "interrupted."
    },
    {
      "start": 207.68,
      "end": 209.7,
      "text": "There's a great deal to come before that."
    },
    {
      "start": 211.62,
      "end": 212.14,
      "text": "Call the witness,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 212.44,
      "end": 213.38,
      "text": "said the king,"
    },
    {
      "start": 213.44,
      "end": 213.84,
      "text": "and the"
    },
    {
      "start": 213.92,
      "end": 216.46,
      "text": "rabbit blew three blasts on the trumpet and called out,"
    },
    {
      "start": 216.54,
      "end": 217.24,
      "text": "First witness."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.66,
      "end": 219.58,
      "text": "The first witness was the"
    },
    {
      "start": 219.64,
      "end": 219.86,
      "text": "hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 220.48,
      "end": 222.68,
      "text": "He came in with a teacup in one hand and"
    },
    {
      "start": 222.68,
      "end": 224.26,
      "text": "a piece of bread and butter in the other."
    },
    {
      "start": 224.93,
      "end": 226.4,
      "text": "I beg your pardon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 226.52,
      "end": 226.9,
      "text": "your majesty,"
    },
    {
      "start": 227.36,
      "end": 227.72,
      "text": "he began,"
    },
    {
      "start": 227.92,
      "end": 229.04,
      "text": "for bringing these in,"
    },
    {
      "start": 229.14,
      "end": 232.14,
      "text": "but I hadn't quite finished my tea when I was sent for."
    },
    {
      "start": 233.34,
      "end": 234.16,
      "text": "You ought to have finished,"
    },
    {
      "start": 234.38,
      "end": 234.88,
      "text": "said the king."
    },
    {
      "start": 235.02,
      "end": 235.84,
      "text": "When did you begin?"
    },
    {
      "start": 237.18,
      "end": 238.58,
      "text": "The hatter looked at the March Hare,"
    },
    {
      "start": 238.78,
      "end": 240.34,
      "text": "who had followed him into the court,"
    },
    {
      "start": 240.42,
      "end": 241.86,
      "text": "arm in arm with the Dormouse."
    },
    {
      "start": 243.2,
      "end": 244.24,
      "text": "Fourteenth of March,"
    },
    {
      "start": 244.4,
      "end": 245.04,
      "text": "I think it was,"
    },
    {
      "start": 245.26,
      "end": 245.76,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 246.36,
      "end": 246.88,
      "text": "Fifteenth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.08,
      "end": 247.92,
      "text": "said the March Hare."
    },
    {
      "start": 248.62,
      "end": 249.24,
      "text": "Sixteenth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.56,
      "end": 250.2,
      "text": "said the Dormouse."
    }
  ]
}